# Proposed changes

Issue Number: close #8421

## Problem summary

1. 当drop库、表、partition的时候，会放到回收站中，并且允许同名信息，通过库、表、partition的id来区分；
2. 增加show dropped命令，可以查看回收站中库、表、partition的信息，包括类型（db、table、partition）、名称、各级id（比如partition除了显示自身的id，还会显示所属库和表的id），删除时间等；
3. 支持recover的时候指定id去恢复，并且支持恢复到一个新名字；如果不指定id，存在多个同名对象时，会恢复最近一次删除的对象；
4. 另外修复了一个原来bug：当drop 库、表、partition的时候，会记录下删除时间，但是这个删除时间没有第一时间记录到auditlog中，而是需要下一次生成新image的时候才会记录到image中。导致如果中间fe重启，会在回放drop的时候，重新生成一个删除时间，之前这种情况影响不大，无非就是彻底删除时间延迟了；但是现在会根据删除时间去判断恢复哪个表的时候，这个时间就要求非常高，因此此次修改，也优化了这个地方，会在drop相关的auditlog中记录下删除时间。如果是force删除，则记录为0。也因此修改了元数据格式，增加了一个元数据版本114。

# Proposed changes

Issue Number: close #12800 

## Problem summary

The `retention` function takes as arguments a set of conditions from 1 to 32 arguments of type `UInt8` that indicate whether a certain condition was met for the event. Any condition can be specified as an argument (as in [WHERE](https://clickhouse.com/docs/en/sql-reference/statements/select/where#select-where)).

The conditions, except the first, apply in pairs: the result of the second will be true if the first and second are true, of the third if the first and third are true, etc.

Syntax
retention(cond1, cond2, ..., cond32);

Arguments
`cond` — An expression that returns a `UInt8` result (1 or 0).

Returned value
The array of 1 or 0.

1 — Condition was met for the event.

select * from tb where a > 'hello' or b < 100;
select * from tb where a > 'hello' or b < 100 or c > 'ok';
select * from tb where (a > 'hello' or b <100) and (a < 'world' or b > 200);
select * from tb where (not a> 'hello') or b < 100;
...

above sql，column `a` and `b` and `c` has created bitmap_index.

title: [improvement](scan) remove concurrency limit if scan has predicate
body:
# Proposed changes

Issue Number: close #12729 

## Problem summary

If a scan node has predicate, we can not limit the concurrency of scanner.
Because we don't know how much data need to be scan.
If we limit the concurrency, this will cause query to be very slow.

For exmple:
`select * from tbl limit 1`, the concurrency will be 1;

title: [Nereids][Improve] infer predicate after push down predicate
body:
# Proposed changes

Issue Number: close #xxx

## Problem summary

This PR implements the function of predicate inference

For example:

``` sql
select * from student left join score on student.id = score.sid where score.sid > 1
```
transformed logical plan tree:

                    left join
             /                    \
       filter(sid >1)     filter(id > 1) <---- inferred predicate
         |                           |
      scan                      scan  

See `InferPredicatesTest`  for more cases

 The logic is as follows:
  1. poll up bottom predicate then infer additional predicates
    for example:
    select * from (select * from t1 where t1.id = 1) t join t2 on t.id = t2.id
    1. poll up bottom predicate
       select * from (select * from t1 where t1.id = 1) t join t2 on t.id = t2.id and t.id = 1
    2. infer
       select * from (select * from t1 where t1.id = 1) t join t2 on t.id = t2.id and t.id = 1 and t2.id = 1
    finally transformed sql:
       select * from (select * from t1 where t1.id = 1) t join t2 on t.id = t2.id and t2.id = 1
  2. put these predicates into `otherJoinConjuncts` , these predicates are processed in the next
    round of predicate push-down


Now only support infer `ComparisonPredicate`.

TODO: We should determine whether `expression` satisfies the condition for replacement
